        <h2>The Solution&colon; How</h2>
        <h3>Empathize</h3>
        <p>The first step I took was to understand Psystem’s competitors, market, and users and further specify the problem to resolve for the website experience by conducting primary and secondary research.</p>
        <h4>Primary Research: Interviewing Psystem’s Founder</h4>
        <p>I conducted primary research by interviewing Psystem’s founder who suffers from chronic pain and the Vice President of Operations who is a caretaker of a loved one who suffers from chronic pain.</p>
        <p>I asked the following questions to learn about their current experience and expectations for the website that has or has yet to be implemented:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>What aspects of the website do you currently like?</li>
            <li>What aspects of the website would you like to see more of?</li>
            <li>What would you like to explore on the Coaching Services page?
            (This question was repeated for all the pages to evaluate what can be improved from its current state.)</li>
            <li>What was something you wanted to learn more about chronic pain management coaching services before the Psystem website was created?</li>
        </ul>
        <p>From the interviews, I learned about the obstacle of not having everything in one place to intuitively find and retrieve when needed, especially when a chronic pain sufferer or their caretaker experiences feelings of discomfort, anxiety, depression, and stress. </p>
        <p>For the business aspect, there was a lack of clarity and cohesiveness on Psystem’s website for chronic pain sufferers and caretakers to quickly find information about services and sign up for a coaching appointment, which would lead to increased conversions.</p>
        <h4>Secondary Research: Understanding what’s “out there”</h4>
        <p>The secondary research focused on finding and learning about health and wellness coaches who have similar business models, needs, and websites to provide both informative and actionable content for visitors to learn about the services and book their first appointment or subscribe to the newsletter.</p>
        <p>I also compared various landing page examples to Psystem’s current page layouts to analyze and create a general outline for an optimized webpage layout to manage user expectations and create a balance of informative content and call-to-action sections for the entire experience.</p>
